Filler Text
Once upon a time there was a guy named Andrew who was browsing Tinder…
he saw the most beautiful girl on Tinder and immediately swiped right.
The girl Jenna thought Andrews opening line was just going to be another dick joke, but instead it was the start of something beautiful…
On December 21st 2014 they decided to meet in person and take a walk to Moore Mesa, where they bonded over their crazy families while watching the sunset.
They both left town during Christmas break but would constantly text and share photos
On January 3rd 2015, they took a moonlit walk along the beach, where they kissed for the first time. Although the beach was cold they stayed out until 4 am.
For their first public date they went to see Gone Girl… big mistake.
Soon after they became smitten and tried to spend as much time together as possible and partook in activities such as…
Bowling, eating, watching soccer, going to the beach and…
Watching The Grand Budapest Hotel. ;)
Things were going swimmingly until Andrew…
broke his ankle and would needed surgery.
Instead of saying peace out, Jenna decided to be an amazing girlfriend and stick by Andrew’s side. She would come over as soon as work and school were done to help nurse him back to health.
She slept over every night, and the best part was in the middle of the night Andrew would wake her up for a quick kiss before letting her drift back to sleep.
Life was easier once Andrew transitioned to a scooter and crutches, they even were able to see book of Mormon, but meeting her family was a struggle with Zeus and the tri level house
Jenna graduated college, and she moved in with Andrew, partially out of love, and being screwed over by a job
At Jenna\'s Graduation party in Sac, Andrew escaped the crowd to the bedroom where he wrote a simple program, to tell Jenna that he loves her.
Life strolled blissfully along, as they enjoyed their life together.
Spring Break 2016, they traveled to D.C. and Albany to see family…
and to NYC where they met up with Alex
In July of 2017, Andrew and Jenna took a plunge and moved to Portland so Andrew could jump start his career.
Not too long after moving, Jenna was able to find a job which she enjoys… for the most part.
They soon came to love Portland with its laid back vibe, food, nature and abundance of activities.
They immersed themselves in the culture and became staunch Blazers fans, who have now attended over 15 games and know whole roster
Over this past winter break, they went off to the east coast again. It was the coldest either had experienced before. Plus weren’t told to pack proper shoes.
Still they had a blast seeing family and friends in New York and Boston. In Boston they met up with Yvette and Tanya where they attended a classy New Years Eve Party
